The seventh hammer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uennder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennder</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/01 5:11:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting over on Rallos</span><hr size=1> start over on tallon or vallos.  Pvp is kind of interesting on rallos until lvl 20 or so, then it more or less stops.  There are a few people that run around attack people while they fight, but in general there is very little pvp on rallos.  On tallon at the very least you can expect to get in a fight almost every single day, and the majority of the time they won't just wait for you to be engaged.  Plus on RZ everyone wears crap gear because they are afraid it will be looted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvividardepericulo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vividar DePericulo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/01 5:58:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting over on Rallos</span><hr size=1> Well... from personal experience, level about 1-10 in misty thicket. Lots of good monsters to kill, very few pks. Some really bad newbie zones are qeynos, Gfay, and nektulos.<br>
<br>
And you can always beg somebody for 7 gold to get a backpack =P<br>
